Russian Railways May Get $1.4 Billion in 2012 Budget, RIA Says

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-08-07T09:35:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/russian-railways-may-get-1-4-billion-in-2012-budget-ria-says.html
OAO Russian Railways expects to
receive at least 40 billion rubles ($1.4 billion) of support in
 Russia ’s 2012 budget, RIA Novosti reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Vladimir Yakunin.  The money is needed “to keep infrastructure and rolling
stock in working condition and a safe state,” Yakunin said at a
press conference in Novosibirsk, Russia, the newswire reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
